  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nContracts are not recompiled after enabling optimizer. I know about `--all` but it'd be nice to recompile contracts after enabling/disabling optimizer or changing `runs`.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n`truffle compile`\r\n\r\nCheck length of `bytecode` in artefacts.\r\n\r\nAdd to config:\r\n```\r\n    solc: {\r\n      optimizer: {\r\n        enabled: true,\r\n        runs: 200\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n`truffle compile`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nLength of `bytecode` less than before\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nLength of `bytecode` the same as before\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: OS X\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Truffle v4.1.6 (core: 4.1.6) Solidity v0.4.21 (solc-js)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v9.2.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 5.8.0\r\n",
